public interface DelegateDataBuilder<T extends Bean>
This interface is designed to support the construction and customization of instances of delegate objects for unit testing. It provides methods for setting properties of the data object to customize the object's properties.

Example implementation

Given the hypothetical data model below:

 ┌───────────────┐               ┌───────────────┐               ┌───────────────┐
 │    EntityA    │ «implements»  │   DelegateX   │  «implements» │    EntityB    │
 │===============│ ────────────▶ │===============│ ◀──────────── │===============│
 │ *NameA        │               │ *Name         │               │ *NameB        │
 └───────────────┘               │ *Currency     │               └───────────────┘
         │                       │ *Percentage   │
         │                       │ *EntityC (FK) │
         │ «implements»          └───────────────┘
         │                              └│┘ n
         │                               │
         ▼                               │  1
 ┌───────────────┐               ┌───────────────┐
 │   DelegateY   │               │    EntityC    │
 │===============│               │===============│
 │ *DateTime     │               │ *NameC        │
 └───────────────┘               └───────────────┘

The corresponding data builder implementation reference would take the following form:


   // Concrete data builder for EntityA
   public class EntityABuilder extends DataBuilder<EntityA, EntityABuilder>
           implements DelegateXBuilder<EntityA, EntityABuilder>, DelegateYBuilder<EntityA, EntityABuilder> {

     public EntityABuilder() {
       super(EntityA.TYPE.get());
     }

     public EntityABuilder withNameA(String nameA) {
       set(EntityA.NAMEA_PROP.get(), nameA);
       return this;
     }
   }

   // Concrete data builder for EntityB
   public class EntityBBuilder extends DataBuilder<EntityB, EntityBBuilder>
           implements DelegateXBuilder<EntityB, EntityBBuilder> {

     public EntityBBuilder() {
       super(EntityB.TYPE.get());
     }

     public EntityBBuilder withNameB(String nameB) {
       set(EntityB.NAMEB_PROP.get(), nameB);
       return this;
     }
   }

   // Concrete data builder for EntityC
   public class EntityCBuilder extends DataBuilder<EntityC, EntityCBuilder> {

     public EntityCBuilder() {
       super(EntityC.TYPE.get());
     }

     public EntityCBuilder withNameC(String nameC) {
       set(EntityC.NAMEC_PROP.get(), nameC);
       return this;
     }

     public <T extends Bean, B extends DelegateXBuilder<T, B>> EntityCBuilder onDelegateX(DelegateXBuilder<T, B> delegateXBuilder) {
       addPopulator(bean -> delegateXBuilder.onEntityC(bean).create());
       return this;
     }
   }

   // Abstract data builder for DelegateX
   @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
   interface DelegateXBuilder<T extends Bean, B extends DelegateXBuilder<T, B>>
           extends DelegateDataBuilder<T> {

     default B withName(String name) {
       set(DelegateX.NAME_DYNPROP, name);
       return (B) this;
     }

     default B withCurrency(Currency currency) {
       set(DelegateX.CURRENCY_DYNPROP, currency);
       return (B) this;
     }

     default B withPercentage(BigDecimal percentage) {
       set(TestDataBuilder_DelegateX.PERCENTAGE_DYNPROP, percentage);
       return (B) this;
     }

     default B onEntityC(EntityC entityC) {
       set(DelegateX.ENTITYC_DYNPROP, entityC);
       return (B) this;
     }

     default B onEntityC(EntityCBuilder entityCBuilder) {
       set(DelegateX.ENTITYC_DYNPROP, entityCBuilder);
       return (B) this;
     }
   }

   // Abstract data builder for DelegateY
   @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
   interface DelegateYBuilder<T extends Bean, B extends DelegateYBuilder<T, B>>
           extends DelegateDataBuilder<T> {

     default B withDateTime(Date date) {
       set(DelegateY.DATETIME_DYNPROP, date);
       return (B) this;
     }
   }

Facilitating the usage of the builder in this manner:


     new EntityABuilder()
             // DelegateX properties
             .withName("Delegate name related to A")
             .withCurrency(Currency.TC_USD)
             .withPercentage(BigDecimal.TEN)
             .onEntityC(new EntityCBuilder()...)

             // DelegateY properties
             .withDateTime(new Date())

             // EntityA properties
             .withNameA("Name for A")

             .createAndCommit();
